description:
SportsDirect.com (Asia) Limited is the newly established division of the Sports Direct International Plc Group. Looking to replicate their success in the EMEA region, the new division is looking to recruit an experienced Graphics Designer.

SportsDirect.com is the UK’s largest sporting goods retailer by revenue. We are proud to operate a diverse portfolio of sports, fitness, fashion and lifestyle retail fascia’s throughout Europe, the U.S and Malaysia and are looking to expand on our success across Asia. We aspire to be a leading sports and lifestyle retailer internationally and need committed and capable candidates to help us achieve our long term strategy.

We are currently searching for an experienced Graphics Designer to join us in our Hong Kong Division. Working as a Graphics Designer, you would be required to liaise with relevant Group departments in the UK and suppliers across China and Asia.

Job Responsibilities:

Responsible for creative concept development and handle all stages of design includes but is not limited to the following:

Brand Guides;

Corporate website;

Social media content (Facebook, Instagram, eDM, Google ad, etc.);

Sales kit and POP materials;

Products retouching and mock-ups;

Online store visual (Web banner, products page, etc.);

Manage ad-hoc projects as assigned.

Handle brand performance and deal with designs on:

Renovate based on the market trend and consumer insights

Communicate with internal and external teams to ensure the great performance of campaigns, advertisements and joint promotion opportunities and POP development

Job Requirements:

Diploma or above in Graphic Design/ Multimedia/ Creative Media or other related disciplines;

5yrs+ graphics and web development experience is preferred;

Exceptional skills in Adobe Suite (Illustrator, Photoshop, InDesign) in Mac environment;

Excellent at preparing presentations and guidelines;

Proficient in animation and video editing is a plus;

Visual merchandising experience is an advantage;

Fluency in English, both written and verbal;

Someone not afraid to raise up and explore different possibilities;

Proven great communication skills knows how to cooperate with different team members and between different departments;

Ability to work in a fast-paced, always shifting environment and taking on new challenges.

If you are a team player with excellent attention to detail and plenty of initiative, this is an excellent opportunity to develop your career within our Group.

 Requirements

- Higher Diploma or above;

- Minimum 2 years cut and sewn knit experience;

- Fluent in spoken and written in English and Mandarin;

- Familiar with MS Office

- Fresh graduates will be considered

- More experience will be Junior Merchandiser

We offer attractive remuneration packages including 13 months payment, medical insurance, annual leave (10~16 days), 10 days wedding leave, education allowance and good career prospects to the right candidate(s). Interested parties, please send your full resume, with expected salary and availability, fax to (852) 2726 7590.

Collected information is strictly for recruitment purpose.

Requirements

-Dipolma or above in Fashion & Textiles, Merchandising & Retailing is preferred;

-Minimum 4 years cut and sewn knit or woven garment merchandising experience;

-Previous experience in high fashion and casual wear is definitely advantage;

-Excellent communication and interpersonal skill with all levels in working with customers, staff and vendors;

-Fluent in spoken and written in English, Chinese and Mandarin;

-Familiar with MS Office operation

-Less experience will be consider to be a Junior Merchandiser

We offer attractive remuneration packages including 13 months payment, 5 days' work, medical insurance, annual leave, wedding leave, education allowance, meal allowance and good career prospects to the right candidate(s). Interested parties, please send your full resume, with expected salary and availability, fax to (852) 2726 7590.

Collected information is only for recruitment purpose.

Responsibilities:

To support the design functions of apparel from analyzing market trend, formulating creative direction to transforming the creative design into marketable collections to our customers
Identifying the market / style needs and creating complete tech packs for fitting / production
Attend overseas fair as well as conduct market visits to obtain the most innovative information
Support the product team to ensure the design is brand appropriate for different region, fashion vision, fit, fabric, color and prints across all categories

Requirements:

Degree holder or above in Fashion Design, Textile & Clothing or related disciplines;
At least 5 years solid experience in apparel (women), with exposure in sports wear will be an advantage;
With strong sense of fashion, materials and yarn, garment technical know-how and graphic artwork application knowledge
Excellent communication & presentation skills;
Strong in handling MAC software, particularly in Illustrator;
Good command in spoken and written Chinese, English and Putonghua;
Frequent travel to China is required

Please  email your CV  for application with expected salary by clicking 'Apply Now'.

(All personal data collected will be used for recruitment purpose only.)

We are looking for candidates with vision, energy and a strong fashion sense who want to be part of a dynamic team and create value. We offer career development as well as regional and local advancement opportunities.

Responsibilities  

Participate in new season collection from sketching, technical drawing, coloring, positioning, trim design, print & pattern graphic illustration, artwork, fitting to sample development stage;
Research and analyze market trends and commercial needs by keeping a consistent brand image and positioning;
Assist in sourcing, selecting and purchasing of fabric for production and color matching for seasonal collection;
Work closely with product development team.

Requirements

Diploma or above in Fashion Design or related discipline;
At least 5 years' relevant experience in ladies' wear Fashion Design in HK or China retail industry;
Creative and respond effectively to the ever-changing consumers’ fashion needs;
Strong passion and sense of fashion;
Good communication and presentation skills;
Able to work independently and good team player;
Proficiency in Photoshop, Illustrator and MS Office applications;
Good command of spoken and written English, Mandarin and Cantonese;
Candidates with less experience will be considered as Fashion Designer.
Interested parties please send your resume with expected salary and portfolio to Human Resources Department via Apply Now.

All information provided will be treated in strict confidence and used solely for recruitment purposes.

